<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>UI/UX Spacing, Padding, and Text Size Demo</title>
    <style>
        .container {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: flex-start;
            width: 300px;
            margin: auto;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .row {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            width: 100%;
        }
        .label {
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .input {
            padding: 5px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 3px;
            width: calc(100% - 10px);
        }
        .button {
            padding: 5px 10px;
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 3px;
            cursor: pointer;
            width: 100%;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <span class="label">Name:</span>
            <input type="text" class="input">
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <span class="label">Email:</span>
            <input type="email" class="input">
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <button class="button">Submit</button>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px;">
        <label for="spacing">Adjust spacing:</label>
        <input type="range" id="spacing" name="spacing" min="0" max="50" value="10" oninput="adjustSpacing(this.value)">
        <br>
        <label for="padding">Adjust padding:</label>
        <input type="range" id="padding" name="padding" min="0" max="20" value="5" oninput="adjustPadding(this.value)">
        <br>
        <label for="textSize">Adjust text size:</label>
        <input type="range" id="textSize" name="textSize" min="8" max="24" value="16" oninput="adjustTextSize(this.value)">
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top: 20px; width: 300px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; font-size: 0.9em;">
        <strong>Explanation:</strong>
        <p><strong>Spacing:</strong> Adjusting the spacing affects the distance between each row of the form. This can impact the readability and visual appeal of the form.</p>
        <p><strong>Padding:</strong> Changing the padding alters the space between the content and the border of the input fields and button. This can influence the overall comfort and aesthetics of the form.</p>
        <p><strong>Text Size:</strong> Modifying the text size adjusts the size of the text within the form elements. This can affect the readability and visual balance of the form.</p>
    </div>
    <script>
        function adjustSpacing(value) {
            var rows = document.querySelectorAll('.row');
            rows.forEach(function(row) {
                row.style.marginBottom = value + 'px';
            });
        }

        function adjustPadding(value) {
            var inputs = document.querySelectorAll('.input');
            var button = document.querySelector('.button');
            inputs.forEach(function(input) {
                input.style.padding = value + 'px';
            });
            button.style.padding = value + 'px 10px';
        }

        function adjustTextSize(value) {
            var container = document.querySelector('.container');
            container.style.fontSize = value + 'px';
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
